A Night at the Opera is the fourth studio album by the British rock band Queen,
released in November 1975. Co-produced by Roy Thomas Baker and Queen, it was the
most expensive album ever recorded at the time of its release. A commercial
success, A Night at the Opera has been voted by the public and cited by music
publications as one of Queen's finest works.
